 <p>

The <b>holy anointing oil</b> described in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../662/9662.xml">
Exodus</link> <weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://php.ug.cs.usyd.edu.au/~jnot4610/bibref.php?book=%20Exodus&amp;verse=30:22-25&amp;src=HE">
30:22-25</weblink> was created from 500 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../827/236827.xml">
shekel</link>s (about 6 kg) of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../861/96861.xml">
myrrh</link>, half as much (about 3 kg) of fragrant <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../469/53469.xml">
cinnamon</link>, 250 shekels (about 3 kg) of fragrant cane, "kaneh bosm," variously translated as <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../540/371540.xml">
calamus</link> or <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../004/2331004.xml">
cannabis</link>),<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> 500 shekels (about 6kg) of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../560/1911560.xml">
cassia</link>, and a hin (about 4 L) of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link>.</p>
